2696/* Do simple CFG optimizations - basic block merging, simplifying of jump
2697 instructions etc. Return nonzero if changes were made. */
2698
2699static bool
2700try_optimize_cfg (int mode)
2701{
2702 bool changed_overall = false;
2703 bool changed;
2704 int iterations = 0;
2705 basic_block bb, b, next;
2706
2707 if (mode & (CLEANUP_CROSSJUMP | CLEANUP_THREADING))
2708 clear_bb_flags ();
2709
2710 crossjumps_occurred = false;
2711
2712 FOR_EACH_BB_FN (bb, cfun)
2713 update_forwarder_flag (bb);
2714
2715 if (! targetm.cannot_modify_jumps_p ())
2716 {
2717 first_pass = true;
2718 /* Attempt to merge blocks as made possible by edge removal. If
2719 a block has only one successor, and the successor has only
2720 one predecessor, they may be combined. */
2721 do
2722 {
2723 block_was_dirty = false;
2724 changed = false;
2725 iterations++;
2726
2727 if (dump_file)
2728 fprintf (dump_file,
2729 "\n\ntry_optimize_cfg iteration %i\n\n",
2730 iterations);
2731
2732 for (b = ENTRY_BLOCK_PTR_FOR_FN (cfun)->next_bb; b
2733 != EXIT_BLOCK_PTR_FOR_FN (cfun);)
2734 {
2735 basic_block c;
2736 edge s;
2737 bool changed_here = false;
2738
2739 /* Delete trivially dead basic blocks. This is either
2740 blocks with no predecessors, or empty blocks with no
2741 successors. However if the empty block with no
2742 successors is the successor of the ENTRY_BLOCK, it is
2743 kept. This ensures that the ENTRY_BLOCK will have a
2744 successor which is a precondition for many RTL
2745 passes. Empty blocks may result from expanding
2746 __builtin_unreachable (). */
2747 if (EDGE_COUNT (b->preds) == 0
2748 || (EDGE_COUNT (b->succs) == 0
2749 && trivially_empty_bb_p (b)
2750 && single_succ_edge (ENTRY_BLOCK_PTR_FOR_FN (cfun))->dest
2751 != b))
2752 {
2753 c = b->prev_bb;
2754 if (EDGE_COUNT (b->preds) > 0)
2755 {
2756 edge e;
2757 edge_iterator ei;
2758
2759 if (current_ir_type () == IR_RTL_CFGLAYOUT)
2760 {
2761 if (BB_FOOTER (b)
2762 && BARRIER_P (BB_FOOTER (b)))
2763 FOR_EACH_EDGE (e, ei, b->preds)
2764 if ((e->flags & EDGE_FALLTHRU)
2765 && BB_FOOTER (e->src) == NULL)
2766 {
2767 if (BB_FOOTER (b))
2768 {
2769 BB_FOOTER (e->src) = BB_FOOTER (b);
2770 BB_FOOTER (b) = NULL;
2771 }
2772 else
2773 {
2774 start_sequence ();
2775 BB_FOOTER (e->src) = emit_barrier ();
2776 end_sequence ();
2777 }
2778 }
2779 }
2780 else
2781 {
2782 rtx_insn *last = get_last_bb_insn (b);
2783 if (last && BARRIER_P (last))
2784 FOR_EACH_EDGE (e, ei, b->preds)
2785 if ((e->flags & EDGE_FALLTHRU))
2786 emit_barrier_after (BB_END (e->src));
2787 }
2788 }
2789 delete_basic_block (b);
2790 changed = true;
2791 /* Avoid trying to remove the exit block. */
2792 b = (c == ENTRY_BLOCK_PTR_FOR_FN (cfun) ? c->next_bb : c);
2793 continue;
2794 }
2795
2796 /* Remove code labels no longer used. */
2797 if (single_pred_p (b)
2798 && (single_pred_edge (b)->flags & EDGE_FALLTHRU)
2799 && !(single_pred_edge (b)->flags & EDGE_COMPLEX)
2800 && LABEL_P (BB_HEAD (b))
2801 && !LABEL_PRESERVE_P (BB_HEAD (b))
2802 /* If the previous block ends with a branch to this
2803 block, we can't delete the label. Normally this
2804 is a condjump that is yet to be simplified, but
2805 if CASE_DROPS_THRU, this can be a tablejump with
2806 some element going to the same place as the
2807 default (fallthru). */
2808 && (single_pred (b) == ENTRY_BLOCK_PTR_FOR_FN (cfun)
2809 || !JUMP_P (BB_END (single_pred (b)))
2810 || ! label_is_jump_target_p (BB_HEAD (b),
2811 BB_END (single_pred (b)))))
2812 {
2813 delete_insn (BB_HEAD (b));
2814 if (dump_file)
2815 fprintf (dump_file, "Deleted label in block %i.\n",
2816 b->index);
2817 }
2818
2819 /* If we fall through an empty block, we can remove it. */
2820 if (!(mode & (CLEANUP_CFGLAYOUT | CLEANUP_NO_INSN_DEL))
2821 && single_pred_p (b)
2822 && (single_pred_edge (b)->flags & EDGE_FALLTHRU)
2823 && !LABEL_P (BB_HEAD (b))
2824 && FORWARDER_BLOCK_P (b)
2825 /* Note that forwarder_block_p true ensures that
2826 there is a successor for this block. */
2827 && (single_succ_edge (b)->flags & EDGE_FALLTHRU)
2828 && n_basic_blocks_for_fn (cfun) > NUM_FIXED_BLOCKS + 1)
2829 {
2830 if (dump_file)
2831 fprintf (dump_file,
2832 "Deleting fallthru block %i.\n",
2833 b->index);
2834
2835 c = ((b->prev_bb == ENTRY_BLOCK_PTR_FOR_FN (cfun))
2836 ? b->next_bb : b->prev_bb);
2837 redirect_edge_succ_nodup (single_pred_edge (b),
2838 single_succ (b));
2839 delete_basic_block (b);
2840 changed = true;
2841 b = c;
2842 continue;
2843 }
2844
2845 /* Merge B with its single successor, if any. */
2846 if (single_succ_p (b)
2847 && (s = single_succ_edge (b))
2848 && !(s->flags & EDGE_COMPLEX)
2849 && (c = s->dest) != EXIT_BLOCK_PTR_FOR_FN (cfun)
2850 && single_pred_p (c)
2851 && b != c)
2852 {
2853 /* When not in cfg_layout mode use code aware of reordering
2854 INSN. This code possibly creates new basic blocks so it
2855 does not fit merge_blocks interface and is kept here in
2856 hope that it will become useless once more of compiler
2857 is transformed to use cfg_layout mode. */
2858
2859 if ((mode & CLEANUP_CFGLAYOUT)
2860 && can_merge_blocks_p (b, c))
2861 {
2862 merge_blocks (b, c);
2863 update_forwarder_flag (b);
2864 changed_here = true;
2865 }
2866 else if (!(mode & CLEANUP_CFGLAYOUT)
2867 /* If the jump insn has side effects,
2868 we can't kill the edge. */
2869 && (!JUMP_P (BB_END (b))
2870 || (reload_completed
2871 ? simplejump_p (BB_END (b))
2872 : (onlyjump_p (BB_END (b))
2873 && !tablejump_p (BB_END (b),
2874 NULL, NULL))))
2875 && (next = merge_blocks_move (s, b, c, mode)))
2876 {
2877 b = next;
2878 changed_here = true;
2879 }
2880 }
2881
2882 /* Try to change a branch to a return to just that return. */
2883 rtx_insn *ret, *use;
2884 if (single_succ_p (b)
2885 && onlyjump_p (BB_END (b))
2886 && bb_is_just_return (single_succ (b), &ret, &use))
2887 {
2888 if (redirect_jump (as_a <rtx_jump_insn *> (BB_END (b)),
2889 PATTERN (ret), 0))
2890 {
2891 if (use)
2892 emit_insn_before (copy_insn (PATTERN (use)),
2893 BB_END (b));
2894 if (dump_file)
2895 fprintf (dump_file, "Changed jump %d->%d to return.\n",
2896 b->index, single_succ (b)->index);
2897 redirect_edge_succ (single_succ_edge (b),
2898 EXIT_BLOCK_PTR_FOR_FN (cfun));
2899 single_succ_edge (b)->flags &= ~EDGE_CROSSING;
2900 changed_here = true;
2901 }
2902 }
2903
2904 /* Try to change a conditional branch to a return to the
2905 respective conditional return. */
2906 if (EDGE_COUNT (b->succs) == 2
2907 && any_condjump_p (BB_END (b))
2908 && bb_is_just_return (BRANCH_EDGE (b)->dest, &ret, &use))
2909 {
2910 if (redirect_jump (as_a <rtx_jump_insn *> (BB_END (b)),
2911 PATTERN (ret), 0))
2912 {
2913 if (use)
2914 emit_insn_before (copy_insn (PATTERN (use)),
2915 BB_END (b));
2916 if (dump_file)
2917 fprintf (dump_file, "Changed conditional jump %d->%d "
2918 "to conditional return.\n",
2919 b->index, BRANCH_EDGE (b)->dest->index);
2920 redirect_edge_succ (BRANCH_EDGE (b),
2921 EXIT_BLOCK_PTR_FOR_FN (cfun));
2922 BRANCH_EDGE (b)->flags &= ~EDGE_CROSSING;
2923 changed_here = true;
2924 }
2925 }
2926
2927 /* Try to flip a conditional branch that falls through to
2928 a return so that it becomes a conditional return and a
2929 new jump to the original branch target. */
2930 if (EDGE_COUNT (b->succs) == 2
2931 && BRANCH_EDGE (b)->dest != EXIT_BLOCK_PTR_FOR_FN (cfun)
2932 && any_condjump_p (BB_END (b))
2933 && bb_is_just_return (FALLTHRU_EDGE (b)->dest, &ret, &use))
2934 {
2935 if (invert_jump (as_a <rtx_jump_insn *> (BB_END (b)),
2936 JUMP_LABEL (BB_END (b)), 0))
2937 {
2938 basic_block new_ft = BRANCH_EDGE (b)->dest;
2939 if (redirect_jump (as_a <rtx_jump_insn *> (BB_END (b)),
2940 PATTERN (ret), 0))
2941 {
2942 if (use)
2943 emit_insn_before (copy_insn (PATTERN (use)),
2944 BB_END (b));
2945 if (dump_file)
2946 fprintf (dump_file, "Changed conditional jump "
2947 "%d->%d to conditional return, adding "
2948 "fall-through jump.\n",
2949 b->index, BRANCH_EDGE (b)->dest->index);
2950 redirect_edge_succ (BRANCH_EDGE (b),
2951 EXIT_BLOCK_PTR_FOR_FN (cfun));
2952 BRANCH_EDGE (b)->flags &= ~EDGE_CROSSING;
2953 std::swap (BRANCH_EDGE (b)->probability,
2954 FALLTHRU_EDGE (b)->probability);
2955 update_br_prob_note (b);
2956 basic_block jb = force_nonfallthru (FALLTHRU_EDGE (b));
2957 notice_new_block (jb);
2958 if (!redirect_jump (as_a <rtx_jump_insn *> (BB_END (jb)),
2959 block_label (new_ft), 0))
2960 gcc_unreachable ();
2961 redirect_edge_succ (single_succ_edge (jb), new_ft);
2962 changed_here = true;
2963 }
2964 else
2965 {
2966 /* Invert the jump back to what it was. This should
2967 never fail. */
2968 if (!invert_jump (as_a <rtx_jump_insn *> (BB_END (b)),
2969 JUMP_LABEL (BB_END (b)), 0))
2970 gcc_unreachable ();
2971 }
2972 }
2973 }
2974
2975 /* Simplify branch over branch. */
2976 if ((mode & CLEANUP_EXPENSIVE)
2977 && !(mode & CLEANUP_CFGLAYOUT)
2978 && try_simplify_condjump (b))
2979 changed_here = true;
2980
2981 /* If B has a single outgoing edge, but uses a
2982 non-trivial jump instruction without side-effects, we
2983 can either delete the jump entirely, or replace it
2984 with a simple unconditional jump. */
2985 if (single_succ_p (b)
2986 && single_succ (b) != EXIT_BLOCK_PTR_FOR_FN (cfun)
2987 && onlyjump_p (BB_END (b))
2988 && !CROSSING_JUMP_P (BB_END (b))
2989 && try_redirect_by_replacing_jump (single_succ_edge (b),
2990 single_succ (b),
2991 (mode & CLEANUP_CFGLAYOUT) != 0))
2992 {
2993 update_forwarder_flag (b);
2994 changed_here = true;
2995 }
2996
2997 /* Simplify branch to branch. */
2998 if (try_forward_edges (mode, b))
2999 {
3000 update_forwarder_flag (b);
3001 changed_here = true;
3002 }
3003
3004 /* Look for shared code between blocks. */
3005 if ((mode & CLEANUP_CROSSJUMP)
3006 && try_crossjump_bb (mode, b))
3007 changed_here = true;
3008
3009 if ((mode & CLEANUP_CROSSJUMP)
3010 /* This can lengthen register lifetimes. Do it only after
3011 reload. */
3012 && reload_completed
3013 && try_head_merge_bb (b))
3014 changed_here = true;
3015
3016 /* Don't get confused by the index shift caused by
3017 deleting blocks. */
3018 if (!changed_here)
3019 b = b->next_bb;
3020 else
3021 changed = true;
3022 }
3023
3024 if ((mode & CLEANUP_CROSSJUMP)
3025 && try_crossjump_bb (mode, EXIT_BLOCK_PTR_FOR_FN (cfun)))
3026 changed = true;
3027
3028 if (block_was_dirty)
3029 {
3030 /* This should only be set by head-merging. */
3031 gcc_assert (mode & CLEANUP_CROSSJUMP);
3032 df_analyze ();
3033 }
3034
3035 if (changed)
3036 {
3037 /* Edge forwarding in particular can cause hot blocks previously
3038 reached by both hot and cold blocks to become dominated only
3039 by cold blocks. This will cause the verification below to fail,
3040 and lead to now cold code in the hot section. This is not easy
3041 to detect and fix during edge forwarding, and in some cases
3042 is only visible after newly unreachable blocks are deleted,
3043 which will be done in fixup_partitions. */
3044 fixup_partitions ();
3045 checking_verify_flow_info ();
3046 }
3047
3048 changed_overall |= changed;
3049 first_pass = false;
3050 }
3051 while (changed);
3052 }
3053
3054 FOR_ALL_BB_FN (b, cfun)
3055 b->flags &= ~(BB_FORWARDER_BLOCK | BB_NONTHREADABLE_BLOCK);
3056
3057 return changed_overall;
3058}

3060/* Delete all unreachable basic blocks. */
3061
3062bool
3063delete_unreachable_blocks (void)
3064{
3065 bool changed = false;
3066 basic_block b, prev_bb;
3067
3068 find_unreachable_blocks ();
3069
3070 /* When we're in GIMPLE mode and there may be debug insns, we should
3071 delete blocks in reverse dominator order, so as to get a chance
3072 to substitute all released DEFs into debug stmts. If we don't
3073 have dominators information, walking blocks backward gets us a
3074 better chance of retaining most debug information than
3075 otherwise. */
3076 if (MAY_HAVE_DEBUG_INSNS && current_ir_type () == IR_GIMPLE
3077 && dom_info_available_p (CDI_DOMINATORS))
3078 {
3079 for (b = EXIT_BLOCK_PTR_FOR_FN (cfun)->prev_bb;
3080 b != ENTRY_BLOCK_PTR_FOR_FN (cfun); b = prev_bb)
3081 {
3082 prev_bb = b->prev_bb;
3083
3084 if (!(b->flags & BB_REACHABLE))
3085 {
3086 /* Speed up the removal of blocks that don't dominate
3087 others. Walking backwards, this should be the common
3088 case. */
3089 if (!first_dom_son (CDI_DOMINATORS, b))
3090 delete_basic_block (b);
3091 else
3092 {
3093 vec<basic_block> h
3094 = get_all_dominated_blocks (CDI_DOMINATORS, b);
3095
3096 while (h.length ())
3097 {
3098 b = h.pop ();
3099
3100 prev_bb = b->prev_bb;
3101
3102 gcc_assert (!(b->flags & BB_REACHABLE));
3103
3104 delete_basic_block (b);
3105 }
3106
3107 h.release ();
3108 }
3109
3110 changed = true;
3111 }
3112 }
3113 }
3114 else
3115 {
3116 for (b = EXIT_BLOCK_PTR_FOR_FN (cfun)->prev_bb;
3117 b != ENTRY_BLOCK_PTR_FOR_FN (cfun); b = prev_bb)
3118 {
3119 prev_bb = b->prev_bb;
3120
3121 if (!(b->flags & BB_REACHABLE))
3122 {
3123 delete_basic_block (b);
3124 changed = true;
3125 }
3126 }
3127 }
3128
3129 if (changed)
3130 tidy_fallthru_edges ();
3131 return changed;
3132}

3134/* Delete any jump tables never referenced. We can't delete them at the
3135 time of removing tablejump insn as they are referenced by the preceding
3136 insns computing the destination, so we delay deleting and garbagecollect
3137 them once life information is computed. */
3138void
3139delete_dead_jumptables (void)
3140{
3141 basic_block bb;
3142
3143 /* A dead jump table does not belong to any basic block. Scan insns
3144 between two adjacent basic blocks. */
3145 FOR_EACH_BB_FN (bb, cfun)
3146 {
3147 rtx_insn *insn, *next;
3148
3149 for (insn = NEXT_INSN (BB_END (bb));
3150 insn && !NOTE_INSN_BASIC_BLOCK_P (insn);
3151 insn = next)
3152 {
3153 next = NEXT_INSN (insn);
3154 if (LABEL_P (insn)
3155 && LABEL_NUSES (insn) == LABEL_PRESERVE_P (insn)
3156 && JUMP_TABLE_DATA_P (next))
3157 {
3158 rtx_insn *label = insn, *jump = next;
3159
3160 if (dump_file)
3161 fprintf (dump_file, "Dead jumptable %i removed\n",
3162 INSN_UID (insn));
3163
3164 next = NEXT_INSN (next);
3165 delete_insn (jump);
3166 delete_insn (label);
3167 }
3168 }
3169 }
3170}

3173/* Tidy the CFG by deleting unreachable code and whatnot. */
3174
3175bool
3176cleanup_cfg (int mode)
3177{
3178 bool changed = false;
3179
3180 /* Set the cfglayout mode flag here. We could update all the callers
3181 but that is just inconvenient, especially given that we eventually
3182 want to have cfglayout mode as the default. */
3183 if (current_ir_type () == IR_RTL_CFGLAYOUT)
3184 mode |= CLEANUP_CFGLAYOUT;
3185
3186 timevar_push (TV_CLEANUP_CFG);
3187 if (delete_unreachable_blocks ())
3188 {
3189 changed = true;
3190 /* We've possibly created trivially dead code. Cleanup it right
3191 now to introduce more opportunities for try_optimize_cfg. */
3192 if (!(mode & (CLEANUP_NO_INSN_DEL))
3193 && !reload_completed)
3194 delete_trivially_dead_insns (get_insns (), max_reg_num ());
3195 }
3196
3197 compact_blocks ();
3198
3199 /* To tail-merge blocks ending in the same noreturn function (e.g.
3200 a call to abort) we have to insert fake edges to exit. Do this
3201 here once. The fake edges do not interfere with any other CFG
3202 cleanups. */
3203 if (mode & CLEANUP_CROSSJUMP)
3204 add_noreturn_fake_exit_edges ();
3205
3206 if (!dbg_cnt (cfg_cleanup))
3207 return changed;
3208
3209 while (try_optimize_cfg (mode))
3210 {
3211 delete_unreachable_blocks (), changed = true;
3212 if (!(mode & CLEANUP_NO_INSN_DEL))
3213 {
3214 /* Try to remove some trivially dead insns when doing an expensive
3215 cleanup. But delete_trivially_dead_insns doesn't work after
3216 reload (it only handles pseudos) and run_fast_dce is too costly
3217 to run in every iteration.
3218
3219 For effective cross jumping, we really want to run a fast DCE to
3220 clean up any dead conditions, or they get in the way of performing
3221 useful tail merges.
3222
3223 Other transformations in cleanup_cfg are not so sensitive to dead
3224 code, so delete_trivially_dead_insns or even doing nothing at all
3225 is good enough. */
3226 if ((mode & CLEANUP_EXPENSIVE) && !reload_completed
3227 && !delete_trivially_dead_insns (get_insns (), max_reg_num ()))
3228 break;
3229 if ((mode & CLEANUP_CROSSJUMP) && crossjumps_occurred)
3230 run_fast_dce ();
3231 }
3232 else
3233 break;
3234 }
3235
3236 if (mode & CLEANUP_CROSSJUMP)
3237 remove_fake_exit_edges ();
3238
3239 /* Don't call delete_dead_jumptables in cfglayout mode, because
3240 that function assumes that jump tables are in the insns stream.
3241 But we also don't _have_ to delete dead jumptables in cfglayout
3242 mode because we shouldn't even be looking at things that are
3243 not in a basic block. Dead jumptables are cleaned up when
3244 going out of cfglayout mode. */
3245 if (!(mode & CLEANUP_CFGLAYOUT))
3246 delete_dead_jumptables ();
3247
3248 /* ??? We probably do this way too often. */
3249 if (current_loops
3250 && (changed
3251 || (mode & CLEANUP_CFG_CHANGED)))
3252 {
3253 timevar_push (TV_REPAIR_LOOPS);
3254 /* The above doesn't preserve dominance info if available. */
3255 gcc_assert (!dom_info_available_p (CDI_DOMINATORS));
3256 calculate_dominance_info (CDI_DOMINATORS);
3257 fix_loop_structure (NULL);
3258 free_dominance_info (CDI_DOMINATORS);
3259 timevar_pop (TV_REPAIR_LOOPS);
3260 }
3261
3262 timevar_pop (TV_CLEANUP_CFG);
3263
3264 return changed;
3265}

3307rtl_opt_pass *
